  <!-- ─── Scaling Plan ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Scaling Plan</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Blueberry's long-term pathway includes the possibility of allocation growth up to <strong>$450,000</strong>. A trader becomes eligible for review after seven payout cycles or $28,000 withdrawn from a single funded account. Eligibility does not guarantee an upgrade — the firm checks strategy, consistency, and behaviour before offering a live account with a $2,000 drawdown and 2 mini or 20 micro capacity.
  </p>

  <!-- ─── Trading Rules ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Trading Rules</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    The rule set focuses on clean behaviour and simple risk control. Only the single max drawdown matters: Ascent checks it at day close, while Accelerated trails it in real time.
  </p>

  <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mb-8">
    <table class="w-full text-sm">
